'''''Tan pel'trokal''''' was a [[Koruun|Korunnal]] word that roughly translated to "jungle justice." It was a form of execution done by the [[Korun/Legends|Korunnai]]: the victims would be taken a hundred [[Kilometer/Legends|kilometers]] from the nearest settlement, removed of all equipment and [[Clothing/Legends|clothing]], and left alone in the [[Jungle/Legends|jungle]], where they faced near-certain [[Death/Legends|death]]. Very few people were known to have survived ''tan pel'trokal''.

[[Liane Trevval|Chalk]] and her [[ghôsh]] dealt ''tan pel'trokal'' upon the [[Balawai]] who had gang-raped her. Kar Vastor considered himself a survivor of ''tan pel'trokal'' after the destruction of his [[Ghôsh Windu|ghôsh]] during the [[Summertime War]], where he exchanged his capacity for [[Human/Legends|Human]] speech for greater power in [[The Force/Legends|the Force]].

